The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Madurai, Oct. 6 (PTI) Two persons were killed and four injured when a bundle of fireworks exploded at Sholavandan railway station near Madurai on Tuesday. The explosion occurred just as a train from which the crackers had been offloaded was leaving the station.           
	The impact of the blast was so intense that the head of one of the victims was blown away while another person was charred beyond recognition, an official said.                   
	 Nagpur (PTI): A young woman Maoist was killed in an encounter in Gadchiroli district on Tuesday, police said. The encounter started when a police team to counter Maoists was on patrol and about 30 to 40 rebels opened fire. The Maoist is yet to be identified.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): An army jawan was seriously injured in a gun battle on Tuesday between militants and security forces in Pulwama, police said. Intermittent firing between the two sides was going on in the forests of Khrew since morning during which the jawan was injured.                   
	 Ludhiana (PTI): A judicial magistrate and his family have been booked under the dowry act and for attempting to murder his wife, who is the daughter of a senior Akali Dal leader in Ludhiana. Magistrate Sukhchain Singh Gill and his two sisters are absconding.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): Bombay High Court has rejected the anticipatory bail application of Congress minister Siddharam Mhetre in a murder case. Mhetre, a minister of state for rural development, is facing charges of instigating the murder of a BJP worker in Solapur last month.                   
	 Barabanki (PTI): Two persons were arrested with 22kg of explosives on Tuesday. Police said, on a tip-off, a house was raided in a village in the Jaidpur police station area and the explosives used in making crackers seized. The arrested duo did not have the licence to make crackers.
                                                                                                                           
